    "name": "Mesh Independence Study for CFD Hemolysis Model",
    "description": "A structured mesh independence study was conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump geometry. Three mesh densities (coarse: 1.2M cells, medium: 4.8M cells, fine: 11.3M cells) were evaluated at the nominal operating condition (2.5 L/min, 2500 RPM). Grid convergence index (GCI) was computed for wall shear stress and velocity magnitude at five cross-sectional planes. The study confirmed that the medium mesh yields a GCI below 3% for all quantities of interest.",
